IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: SCHOLARSHIPS TO STUDENTS AND SUPPORT TO GARRETT COLLEGE
IRS990.MissionDesc: TO SUPPORT THE COLLEGE IN ITS STUDENT ENROLLMENT EFFORTS VIA MONETARY SOLICITATIONS,AND OTHER CHARITABLE GIVING TO MAKE AVAILABLE SCHOLARSHIPS, AND OTHER FINANCIAL SUPPORT TO THE INSTITUTION.
IRS990.Desc: SCHOLARSHIPS TO STUDENTS IN SUPPORT OF CONTINUING POST-SECONDARY EDUCATION AT GARRETT COLLEGE.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: OWN STUDENT HOUSING FACILITY LEASED TO AFFILIATED COLLEGE AND SERVICE DEBT ASSOCIATED WITH CONSTRUCTION INDEBTEDNESS.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: MOSSER ROAD HERITAGE TRAIL WAS DEVELOPED ALONG WITH COMMUNITY SUPPORT TO IMPROVE THE SAFETY OF THE STUDENTS WHO WALK ALONG MOSSER ROAD.

ProgSrvcAccomActyOtherGrp.Desc: OTHER PROGRAM SERVICES INCLUDES THE NEW PERFORMING ARTS CENTER AND OTHER GARRETT COLLEGE PROGRAMS FOR THE STUDENTS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ENDOWMENT FUNDS ARE USED TO FUND STUDENT SCHOLARSHIPS AND SUPPORT OTHER GARRETT COLLEGE PROGRAM ACTIVITIES.

UNDER GAAP, AN ORGANIZATION MUST RECOGNIZE THE TAX BENEFIT ASSOCIATED WITH TAX POSITIONS TAKEN FOR TAX RETURN PURPOSES WHEN IT IS MORE LIKELY THAN NOT THE POSITION WILL BE SUSTAINED. THE ORGANIZATION DOES NOT BELIEVE THERE ARE ANY MATERIAL UNCERTAIN TAX POSTIONS AND, ACCORDINGLY, IT WILL NOT RECOGNIZE ANY LIABILITY FOR UNRECOGNIZED TAX LIABILITES.

STATE MATCHING GRANT FUNDS INCLUDED IN SCHOLARSHIP FUNDS ARE MONITORED FOR COMPLIANCE WITH EXPENDITURE REQUIREMENTS CONSISTENT WITH THE TERMS OF STATE OF MARYLAND INFORMATION PARTNERSHIP FOR TECHNOLOGY(IPT)MATCHING GRANT PROGRAM.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE DRAFT FORM 990 IS REVIEWED BY TREASURER OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS AND EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR; AND IT IS MADE AVAILABLE TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS ELECTRONICALLY PRIOR TO FILING WITH THE IRS. THE RETURN IS THEN PRESENTED TO THE FULL BOARD AT THE NEXT REGULARLY SCHEDULED QUARTERLY MEETING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BY-LAWS ESTABLISH GUIDELINES WITH RESPECT TO CONFLICTS OF INTEREST AND REQUIRE DISCLOSURE OF ALL SUCH INSTANCES BY OFFICERS AND DIRECTORS. IN ADDITION, AN ANNUAL CONFLICT OF INTEREST QUESTIONAIRE IS COMPLETED BY ALL OFFICERS AND DIRECTORS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON RECEIPT OF REQUEST.
THE ORGANIZATION HAS NOT CHANGED ITS OVERSIGHT PROCESS OR SELECTION PROCESS DURING THE YEAR.
